  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db4\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dbd\u0dca 200\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d85\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dd4\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "200 rupees less fuel can be given",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Janaka Ratnayake, chairman of the Public Utilities Commission, said today (7) that it is possible to provide a liter of fuel to the people at a price 200 rupees lower than the current price. While holding a special press conference in Colombo, he mentioned that the actual import cost of a liter of fuel is below 300 rupees.",
        "He noted that a barrel of 92 octane petrol was imported at $100, a barrel of octane 95 petrol at $103, a barrel of auto diesel at $112, a barrel of super diesel at $115 and a barrel of kerosene at $105. He pointed out that the fuel price formula should be calculated according to the import value.",
        "Meanwhile, in a press conference held recently, the Minister of Electricity and Energy Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera said that if it is the chairman of the Public Utilities Commission or someone else who is willing to provide fuel above the existing price, he is ready to appoint that person as the chairman of the Petroleum Corporation."
      ],
